'''Marcia Lucas''' (née Griffin; born [[October 4]], [[1945]]) is an American film editor. She met [[George Lucas]] when [[Wikipedia:Verna Fields|Verna Fields]] hired her to work as an assistant editor to George while editing [[Wikipedia:United States Information Agency|United States Information Agency]] documentaries, and they were married from [[1960s|1969]] to [[1983]]. They adopted one daughter, [[Amanda Lucas|Amanda]], who was born in [[1981]].

Marcia was a co-editor on [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|'' A New Hope'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|'' Return of the Jedi'']] (with some uncredited work on [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|'' The Empire Strikes Back'']] as well). She won an Academy Award for her work on ''A New Hope'', which was shared with [[Paul Hirsch]] and [[Richard Chew]].

